Factors we must consider are demand, lead time, the extent of variability of lead time and demand, and the acceptable level of stock-out risk.

We have to know what our estimated demand during lead time is for our product so we know how much to order between order points.

The variability of our demand and lead time will help us deterime how much safety stock we will need to have. If we have a high variabiliy, we may need to have more safety stock, if we have a low variability we may need to have less safety stock.
